<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 07 at 1:01AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Blowing snow across northern portions of Toole and Liberty Counties...
At 1255 am MST...Southerly winds gusting between 20 and 40 mph
across northern portions of Toole and Liberty Counties are causing
blowing snow there. This includes the Sweet Grass Hills area. Web
camera imagery at the Port of Sweet Grass is showing reduced
visibility at the Canadian Border.
If you will be traveling across this area tonight, stay aware of
rapidly changing visibility and road conditions due to the blowing
snow. Also, do not use your high beam headlights, as the
dispersion of the bright light will make it even more difficult to
see.</description>
